The MEHO-authored minimal OpenAPI specs and ExecutionProfiles shipped
as package data for the vmware/9.0 and sddc/9.0 catalog rows
(src/meho_backplane/operations/ingest/specs/{vmware_rest,sddc_manager}_minimal.yaml
and src/meho_backplane/connectors/profiles/{vmware_rest,sddc_manager}_minimal.yaml)
reproduce vendor API path/parameter/field names verbatim for
interoperability (the dispatcher must address the appliance by its real
names). They are Apache-2.0, evoila-authored, carry vendor-neutral
MEHO-authored descriptions, and do NOT redistribute the full vendor
specs (kept as upstream provenance pointers). See
docs/decisions/shipped-spec-provenance.md for the derivative-work /
interoperability provenance record and human signoff of record.
